    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The infographic follows a narrative structure designed to tell a story. It begins with a strong visual hook (the "Two Paths" chart) to establish the core thesis. It then provides essential context (The Klondike Gold Rush) using high-impact stats. The central section is an interactive flowchart visualizing the "Formation of White Fang," allowing users to explore the cause-and-effect relationship between environment and behavior. The final section covers the publication and legacy. This structure transforms the dense report into an engaging, digestible journey for the user, prioritizing narrative flow over the original document's layout. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        1. Report Info: "Inverse process" comparison to "The Call of the Wild". Goal: Compare. Viz/Method: Line Chart (Chart.js). Justification: A line chart visually and immediately communicates the opposing trajectories of the two protagonists, which is the report's central analytical point.
        2. Report Info: Klondike Gold Rush statistics. Goal: Inform. Viz/Method: Large number callouts (HTML/CSS). Justification: Conveys the scale and difficulty of the historical event with maximum impact and minimal clutter.
        3. Report Info: Table 2 (Formation of White Fang). Goal: Organize/Show Process. Viz/Method: Interactive flowchart using structured HTML/CSS with Tailwind. Justification: Transforms a static table into an engaging, user-driven exploration of the protagonist's development, reinforcing the theme of environmental influence.
        4. Report Info: Table 1 (Publication Chronology). Goal: Change/Show Time. Viz/Method: Vertical timeline using HTML/CSS. Justification: Clearly and cleanly presents chronological data in a universally understood format.
    -->
